{"title":"Keep one Netbeans icon in your OS X Finder Dock","headings":[],"date":"2011-10-27T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["os x"],"body":{"tag":"div","children":[{"tag":"p","children":["After installing Netbeans, you drag the Netbeans.app in your dock. And each time\nyou start Netbeans, you have a second Netbeans icon which appears… That’s\nboring."]},"\n",{"tag":"p","children":["Here is the solution :"]},"\n",{"tag":"p","children":["Go into the ",{"tag":"code","children":["/Applications/Netbeans"]}," folder, and open the Netbeans package."]},"\n",{"tag":"figure","props":{"class":"flex-media--unknown"},"children":["\n  ",{"tag":"img","props":{"class":"flex-media__item","src":"/media/2011/10/open-netbeans-package.png","alt":"","title":"Open Netbeans.app package"}},"\n"]},"\n",{"tag":"p","children":["Then open ",{"tag":"code","children":["etc/netbeans.conf"]}]},"\n",{"tag":"figure","props":{"class":"flex-media--unknown"},"children":["\n  ",{"tag":"img","props":{"class":"flex-media__item","src":"/media/2011/10/open-netbeans-conf.png","alt":"","title":"Edit netbeans.conf"}},"\n"]},"\n",{"tag":"p","children":["You should see in the file :"]},"\n",{"tag":"pre","children":[{"tag":"code","props":{"class":"hljs language-bash"},"children":[{"tag":"span","props":{"class":"hljs-comment"},"children":["# Default location of JDK, can be overridden by using --jdkhome [<dir>:"]},"\n",{"tag":"span","props":{"class":"hljs-comment"},"children":["#netbeans_jdkhome=\"/path/to/jdk\""]}]}]},"\n",{"tag":"p","children":["Just add\n",{"tag":"code","children":["netbeans_jdkhome=\"/System/Library/Frameworks/JavaVM.framework/Versions/CurrentJDK/Home/\""]},"\nafter theses lines."]},"\n",{"tag":"p","children":["Restart Netbeans and voilà !"]}]}}